Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.25,0:00:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In the year 845,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.83,0:00:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the Colossal Titan and the\NArmored Titan suddenly appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.62,0:00:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and destroyed one of humanity's\Nwalls--and everyday life with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.33,0:00:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Humanity abandoned Wall Maria,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.58,0:00:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,lost 20% of its population\Nand one-third of its territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.37,0:00:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and was forced to\Nretreat behind Wall Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.95,0:00:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, in the year 850, in Trost District...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.37,0:00:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again, humanity allowed the\NTitans to further their advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.29,0:00:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And Eren Jaeger,\Nwho had fallen prey to one,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.50,0:01:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,reappeared from inside\Na mysterious Titan...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.70,0:01:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Unknown are the names{\i0}\N{\i1}of the flowers that have been trampled{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.75,0:01:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Birds have fallen to the earth{\i0}\N{\i1}and long for the wind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.20,0:01:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Prayers won't solve anything{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.29,0:01:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Only the will to fight{\i0}\N{\i1}can change the here and now!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.62,0:01:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}O pigs who laugh at the resolve{\i0}\N{\i1}to walk over corpses to move forward{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.91,0:01:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Livestock complacency? False prosperity?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.45,0:01:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Give us the freedom of dying,{\i0}\N{\i1}starving wolves!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.33,0:01:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The humiliation of being caged{\i0}\N{\i1}is what triggers us to fight back{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.70,0:02:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We hunters slaughter prey{\i0}\N{\i1}beyond the castle walls,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.04,0:02:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}consumed with surging bloodlust,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.25,0:02:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}as our crimson bows and arrows{\i0}\N{\i1}pierce scarlet holes into the twilight{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.41,0:02:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,"Response"\N"The Struggle for Trost, Part 6"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.79,0:02:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask one more time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.62,0:02:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.50,0:02:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm human!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.54,0:02:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.91,0:02:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't take this personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.54,0:03:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Marco...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.58,0:03:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do this anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.87,0:03:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't fight Titans anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.37,0:03:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What's gotten into you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.83,0:03:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,My friends got\Neaten right in front of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.87,0:03:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My friends got killed, yet I didn't\Nfeel any sadness or hate at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.04,0:03:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Deep down,\NI just felt glad it wasn't me...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.62,0:03:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's my turn next.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.41,0:03:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I've realized what our job is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.25,0:03:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's basically fighting and fighting\Nuntil we eventually get eaten!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.95,0:03:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, screw that! I'd rather end things now...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.62,0:03:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! Pull yourself together!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.08,0:03:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You aren't the only one, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.70,0:03:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We're {\i1}all {\i0}fighting back fear!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.45,0:03:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at Sasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.79,0:03:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after what she went through,\Nshe's still an upstanding soldier!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.20,0:03:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... My stomach hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.25,0:03:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please consider\Nme one of the wounded?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.41,0:03:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,--I can't go on!\N--Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.45,0:03:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.79,0:04:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That gag order is\Ndefinitely warranted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.16,0:04:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The situation's bad enough as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.04,0:04:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If they found out about Eren...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.45,0:04:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Cannon fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.91,0:04:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why only one shot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.45,0:04:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! Smoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.45,0:04:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's {\i1}inside {\i0}the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.04,0:04:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,--Hey!\N--What's happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.20,0:04:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.58,0:04:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they break through the water gate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible!\NThat's the sturdiest place of all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.29,0:04:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They must've just\Nset off a shell by accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.58,0:04:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.95,0:04:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why's there so much smoke?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.75,0:04:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No way... Is it Titan steam?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.08,0:04:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.79,0:04:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.83,0:05:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.00,0:05:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.54,0:05:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain Woermann!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.58,0:05:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Wait and see what it does!\NWe can't risk getting near it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.33,0:05:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay on alert, everyone!\NRemain on standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.83,0:05:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Artillerymen, reload the cannon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.04,0:06:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What is {\i1}this{\i0}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.58,0:06:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I remember hearing the cannon go off...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.33,0:06:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,After that came a tremendous\Nsound, shock, and heat!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.04,0:06:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we're inside a giant skeleton--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.83,0:06:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Eren protected us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.45,0:06:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all we need to understand for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.62,0:06:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Flowers, only on the inside...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.29,0:06:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.87,0:06:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.91,0:06:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Eren! What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.87,0:06:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.04,0:07:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's already starting to vaporize,\Njust like a Titan's corpse!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.04,0:07:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get away from it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.91,0:07:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't tell if they're watching\Nand waiting or if they're in a daze...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.25,0:07:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The Garrison Regiment isn't\Nshowing any signs of activity for now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.16,0:07:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,...but I'm sure they'll start\Nattacking again soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.29,0:07:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt there's {\i1}any {\i0}chance of reasoning\Nwith them now, after seeing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.58,0:07:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But there {\i1}is {\i0}one\Nthing I remember now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.95,0:07:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.37,0:07:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The basement of my house!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.54,0:07:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad said it'd all\Nmake sense if I go there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.41,0:07:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He's also the reason\Nthis has happened to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.75,0:07:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If I go to the basement, I might\Nfigure out what the Titans are too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.62,0:07:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why did he keep it a secret?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.91,0:07:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands of Scouts have\Ndied trying to get that information!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.04,0:07:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only hope humanity has!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.29,0:08:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And he just kept it tucked away\Nin our basement all this time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.20,0:08:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell was he thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.41,0:08:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And where the hell has\Nhe been these last five years--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.87,0:08:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Eren.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.66,0:08:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We have other things to attend to right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.20,0:08:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.45,0:08:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The smoke's clearing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.66,0:08:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack on sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.75,0:08:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's finish it off quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.83,0:08:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold your positions!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.70,0:08:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.75,0:08:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,--And going where? How?!\N--Anywhere will do for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.16,0:08:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll go over the wall and\Nmake for the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,After I've changed into a Titan again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.54,0:08:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you really do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.00,0:08:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how I'm doing it, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.25,0:08:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know I can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.70,0:08:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like how I can't really\Nexplain how I'm moving my arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.50,0:09:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Just now, my mind unconsciously\Nfocused on stopping the cannonball.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.75,0:09:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it decayed; it only had\Nthe capabilities and endurance for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.87,0:09:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time I'm gonna\Nbe an even stronger one...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.41,0:09:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna be a 15 meter-high one\Nthat can slaughter other Titans, like before!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.41,0:09:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Eren!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.25,0:09:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Your nose is bleeding...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.20,0:09:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You look really pale,\Nand your breathing is rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.29,0:09:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's clearly wrong!\NYou're not well!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.87,0:09:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My health doesn't matter right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.50,0:09:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I have two ideas in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.79,0:09:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys can get through this\Nalive if you stop trying to protect me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.91,0:09:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already caused\Nyou enough trouble as it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.91,0:09:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'm gonna go\Nit alone from here on out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.62,0:09:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.16,0:09:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,--I--\N--Eren.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.58,0:09:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.58,0:09:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:10:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't keep up,\Nyou won't have to worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.25,0:10:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But I won't have to\Ndo what you say, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.37,0:10:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm serious here!\NJust forget about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.00,0:10:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not your little brother or your kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.20,0:10:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.62,0:10:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir. The cannon is almost reloaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.66,0:10:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What are your next attack orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.70,0:10:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You will wait for my signal!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.58,0:10:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.50,0:10:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, the Garrison Regiment\Nisn't showing any signs
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.66,0:10:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of launching a close-quarters assault.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.91,0:10:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If they were, Mikasa would've\Nsensed it faster than a stray cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.20,0:10:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Assuming they reload in\Nthe shortest time possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.37,0:10:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,...it'll take them about twenty more seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.04,0:10:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I figure Eren will spring into\Naction and be gone before then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.41,0:11:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why am I reminded\Nof that at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.45,0:11:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it... because\Nthis is the end for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.87,0:11:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In the very end,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.87,0:11:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I never amounted to\Nanything more than a coward...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.95,0:11:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They were there to\Nhelp me so many times...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.12,0:11:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,...but not once did\NI ever manage to help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.62,0:11:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I possibly\Ncall myself an equal friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.29,0:11:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I possibly\Noffer to go with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.66,0:11:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not even confident\NI can keep up...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.79,0:11:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess this is the last time...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.00,0:12:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,...the three of us will ever be together...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.41,0:12:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Eren. I {\i1}am{\i0}--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.41,0:12:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Mikasa!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.45,0:12:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I had {\i1}two {\i0}ideas, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.95,0:12:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Armin. I leave the decision to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.79,0:12:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.79,0:12:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I know how unrealistic this plan is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.54,0:12:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The best option would\Nbe to use this Titan ability
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.54,0:12:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in a systematic way,\Nunder the military's direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.62,0:12:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this sounds crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.00,0:12:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you think you can convince the\NGarrison Regiment that I'm not a threat,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.95,0:12:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll trust in you and go with that option.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.04,0:12:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my second idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.95,0:12:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't think you can do it,\NI'll go with the other idea as a last resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.25,0:12:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Decide in fifteen seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.95,0:12:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do it or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.95,0:12:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll respect your opinion,\Nwhichever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.54,0:13:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Eren...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.33,0:13:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you entrusting such an\Nimportant decision to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.16,0:13:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when things get ugly,\Nyou always make the right call, y'know?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.79,0:13:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I figure that's worth relying on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.12,0:13:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When did I ever do that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.00,0:13:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All the time.\NLike that time five years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.75,0:13:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hadn't gone and\Ngotten Mr. Hannes for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.00,0:13:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mikasa and I would've been Titan food.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.41,0:13:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all in my head... I convinced\Nmyself that's how I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.58,0:13:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I convinced myself\NI was helpless and a burden...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.62,0:13:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But they never felt that way at all...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.50,0:13:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Armin! We're out of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.62,0:14:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They've finished reloading, Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.79,0:14:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We can fire at any time!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.83,0:14:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,These two who are willing\Nto place their lives in my hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.50,0:14:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,...are the people I trust\Nmore than anyone in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.87,0:14:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What more convincing\Ndo I need than that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.50,0:14:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I {\i1}will {\i0}persuade them, without fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.91,0:14:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll need you to act as\Nnonaggressive as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.25,0:14:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's been bugging me ever\Nsince Eren started fighting as a Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.58,0:14:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't collected my\Nthoughts yet, but I'll do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.37,0:14:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to think as I talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.29,0:14:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Halt!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.37,0:14:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You've finally revealed your true form, monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.25,0:15:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it! I'll give the signal to fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.58,0:15:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He is {\i1}not {\i0}an enemy of humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.08,0:15:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We're willing to disclose\Neverything we've learned!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.58,0:15:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Begging for your lives won't help you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.83,0:15:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He's revealed his true form for\Nall to see! What more is there to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.75,0:15:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you insist he's not our enemy,\Nthen show me proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.66,0:15:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't, then we'll simply\Neliminate the threat he poses!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.16,0:15:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need for proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.66,0:15:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right... There {\i1}is {\i0}no need!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.58,0:15:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, this isn't about\Nwhat {\i1}we {\i0}perceive him to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.00,0:15:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.16,0:15:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear that countless people saw him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.16,0:15:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In which case, they surely\Nsaw him fighting Titans as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.45,0:15:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And they must've seen the\NTitans swarming around him too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the Titans saw\Nhim as prey--just like they see us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.37,0:15:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an irrefutable fact,\Nhowever hard you look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.37,0:16:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He has a point...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.16,0:16:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,--A Titan, on our side?\N--That's crazy...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.00,0:16:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.95,0:16:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be taken in\Nby their clever ruses!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.83,0:16:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Their behavior has always\Nbeen beyond our understanding!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.29,0:16:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's entirely possible they'd take on\Nhuman form and use human language
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.08,0:16:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to deceive us all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.08,0:16:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't let them have their way anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.79,0:16:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no use...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.87,0:16:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He's abandoned all logic...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.33,0:16:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He's afraid to think...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.20,0:16:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Eren! Mikasa!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.16,0:17:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,As a soldier, I have\Nlong sworn to give my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.04,0:17:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for the restoration of humankind!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.00,0:17:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing would make me\Nhappier than to die for that cause!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.58,0:17:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If we combine his Titan ability\Nwith our own remaining manpower,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.29,0:17:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we {\i1}can {\i0}retake this city!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.62,0:17:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,For humanity's glory,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.83,0:17:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in what little time I have left to live,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.75,0:17:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I will continue to\Nadvocate his strategic value!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.12,0:17:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain Woermann.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.00,0:17:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe his words are worth consid--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.75,0:17:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.75,0:17:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,However much they beg\Nfor their lives, they're still traitors...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.41,0:17:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To dispose of those who violate the rules...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.79,0:17:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the duty of a soldier!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.75,0:17:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.70,0:17:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you're still as delicate\Nas a young deer despite your size.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.95,0:17:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander Pyxis...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.62,0:18:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you not see that\Nsoldier's splendid salute?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.75,0:18:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I've only just arrived, but I've\Nbeen filled in on the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.50,0:18:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in charge of\Nthe reinforcements now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.12,0:18:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Something tells me we ought\Nto hear these people out, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.54,0:18:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the\NScout Regiment's reports,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.33,0:18:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it was believed that the\NTitans would appear from the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, it was Shiganshina District,\Non the south side of Wall Maria,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.41,0:18:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Titans attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.41,0:18:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the fortified city of Trost\Non the south side of Wall Rose
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.95,0:18:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,was deemed their next most likely target.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.16,0:18:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"Trost District, Inner Gate"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.08,0:18:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Dot Pyxis...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.33,0:19:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The top officer in charge of Trost\Nand the entire southern territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.08,0:19:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and the man given full authority for the\Ndefense of humanity's most vital region.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.87,0:19:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope, none at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.83,0:19:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I certainly wouldn't mind being\Ngobbled up by a beautiful girl Titan...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.95,0:19:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's also known for\Nbeing a full-blown eccentric.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.58,0:19:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the commander thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.37,0:19:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking those freaks up\Nthere without a single bodyguard...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.20,0:19:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. He's never\Nbeen one to make much sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.83,0:19:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.12,0:19:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We've finished reassembling the troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.12,0:19:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.29,0:19:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.75,0:19:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.25,0:19:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And visiting this basement will\Nmake everything clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.95,0:19:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... Do you believe me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.25,0:19:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing as you, yourself,\Nare unable to provide validation,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.83,0:20:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,for now I'm simply\Nkeeping it all in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.12,0:20:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do believe I can tell when\Nsomeone is being sincere or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.66,0:20:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I will personally guarantee your safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.41,0:20:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Cadet Arlelt, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.41,0:20:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.66,0:20:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, you mentioned that\Nwith this so-called "Titan ability"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.25,0:20:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be possible to retake this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.75,0:20:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you truly believe that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.79,0:20:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Or was that just a\Ndesperate plea for your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.87,0:20:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.33,0:20:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Both.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.50,0:20:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to suggest that Eren,\Nin Titan form, could take that giant rock
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.54,0:20:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and use it to block the wrecked entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.41,0:20:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just an idea\NI came up with on the spot...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.20,0:20:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted them to see\Nthe possibilities of Eren's ability
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.45,0:20:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it could help\Nsolve the situation we're in...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.95,0:21:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I was\Ndesperate to survive, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.79,0:21:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"Desperate to survive..."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.12,0:21:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing more\Ncredible than those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.58,0:21:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say, Cadet Jaeger?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.91,0:21:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.50,0:21:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you plug the hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.87,0:21:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... Uhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.45,0:21:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.04,0:21:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, I don't really understand\Nany more than the rest of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.79,0:21:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I can. Maybe I can't. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.75,0:21:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't feel I can risk\Ngiving an irresponsible answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.04,0:21:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes. My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.91,0:21:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked the wrong question.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.12,0:21:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Will {\i0}you do it or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.04,0:22:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.87,0:22:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.33,0:22:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if\NI can plug the hole or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.20,0:22:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.66,0:22:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.79,0:22:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your dreams are where your heart is{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.91,0:23:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're more fragile than life itself{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.16,0:23:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Over and over you cast them aside,{\i0}\N{\i1}only to find more{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.83,0:23:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now, rest in peace{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.50,0:23:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Pounding impulses defile the things we wish for{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.83,0:23:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and the more we forget{\i0}\N{\i1}the more we remember again{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.12,0:23:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In this beautiful, cruel world{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.08,0:23:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}all I can do is ask why we're still alive{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.25,0:23:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh, with our strength--and our weakness--{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.95,0:23:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}what are we going to protect if there's no sense{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.62,0:24:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to anything anymore?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.62,0:24:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite having fled\Nout of fear once before,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.25,0:24:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the soldiers choose to\Nstand on the battlefield again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.66,0:24:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Eren makes up his mind:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.16,0:24:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'll be everyone's hope."
